<note>Story of a hunter, who met the Buddha while hunting, he couldn't find animals accept the Buddha sitting under a Bodhi tree. When he tried to shoot the Buddha with his arrows, his arms and body were dead (couldn't move). His wife, their seven children and wives followed and tried to the same but all faced the same problem. Eventually the Buddha taught them and all attained 'Sot&#x101;panna' the Stream Entrance to the Enlightenment.</note>
